main event: A sighting of an unidentified flying object was reported in Lancaster, PA on February 23.
interesting points: The object was orange in color and estimated to be three times the size of a star., The object was observed for several minutes at 30 degrees above the horizon., It hovered for about 45 minutes before flying out of sight to the west., The weather conditions were clear with good visibility at the time of the sighting., The report concluded there was insufficient data for evaluation.
witness description: The witness reported the sighting and described the object's size and color.
